<h1 class='center-h'>Contributing</h1>

<p>
Help is always welcome and there are plenty of options how you can contribute to SymOntoClay.
</p>

<p>
In particular, your contribution would be helpful in the following areas:
    <ul>
	    <li>
		    Trying to use SymOntoClay.
		</li>
		<li>
		    Reporting <a href='https://github.com/Symontoclay/SymOntoClay/issues'>issues</a>.
		</li>
		<li>
		    Fixing and responding to <a href='https://github.com/Symontoclay/SymOntoClay/issues'>SymOntoClay’s GitHub issues</a>.
		</li>
		<li>
		    Improving the documentation, especially fixing grammar issues. 
			I am not a native English speaker, so there are a lot of grammar mistakes in SymOntoClay's documentation.
		</li>
		<li>
		    Getting involved in the language design process by proposing language changes or new features in <a href='https://github.com/Symontoclay/SymOntoClay/discussions'>the SymOntoClay’s forum</a> and providing feedback.
		</li>
		<li>
		    Getting involved in improving the design process: all ideas are welcome.
		</li>
		<li>
		    Getting involved in creating new features. There are also many sub-areas in the big area:
			
			<ul>
			    <li>
				    Implementing new language features
				</li>
			    <li>
				    Implementing new engine features
				</li>
			    <li>
				    Improving performance
				</li>
			    <li>
				    Improving integration with Unity
				</li>
			    <li>
				    Creating extensions for code editors.
					First of all SymOntoClay needs extensions for Visual Studio and Visual Studio Code.
				</li>	
			    <li>
				    Improving DevOps
				</li>
			    <li>
				    Redesign the SymOntoClay’s site.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>		
	</ul>
</p>

<p>
Please note that this project is released with a <a href='https://github.com/Symontoclay/SymOntoClay/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md'>Contributor Code of Conduct</a>. 
By participating in this project - in the <a href='https://github.com/Symontoclay/SymOntoClay/issues'>issues</a>, <a href='https://github.com/Symontoclay/SymOntoClay/pulls'>pull requests</a>, or <a href='https://github.com/Symontoclay/SymOntoClay/discussions'>Discussion</a> - you agree to abide by its terms.
</p>
